************** G E N E R A L   I N F O R M A T I O N *************6522 1451   28
                                                                  6522 1451   29
This evaluated data file is based on a software system built      6522 1451   30
around the nuclear model code TALYS [kon07], version 1.74. It is  6522 1451   31
part of a large collection of isotopic evaluations, all created by6522 1451   32
running the system with either adjusted or default input          6522 1451   33
parameters. This means that the data in the entire collection have6522 1451   34
been tested in detail for many isotopes against individual        6522 1451   35
experimental data, while for other isotopes it is only as good as 6522 1451   36
the global quality of TALYS at the moment. The mutual quality of  6522 1451   37
all individual data files is however consistent: The same set of  6522 1451   38
nuclear models is used and, equally important, the same ENDF-6    6522 1451   39
formatting procedures for each isotope. The data file has been    6522 1451   40
created automatically using the ENDF-6 format generator TEFAL.    6522 1451   41
                                                                  6522 1451   42
The resulting data file provides a complete representation of     6522 1451   43
nuclear data needed for transport, activation, damage, heating,   6522 1451   44
radioactivity, and shielding applications over the incident       6522 1451   45
neutron energy range from 1.e-11 to 200. MeV.                     6522 1451   46
                                                                  6522 1451   47
All transport and activation data for neutrons, charged particles,6522 1451   48
photons and residual nuclides are filed. This includes cross      6522 1451   49
sections, angular distributions, double-differential spectra,     6522 1451   50
isomeric production, discrete and continuum photon production     6522 1451   51
cross sections, residual production cross sections and recoils.   6522 1451   52
This general purpose evaluation can thus be used as both          6522 1451   53
transport and activation library.                                 6522 1451   54
                                                                  6522 1451   55
A complete set of covariance data is included, which is stored    6522 1451   56
in MF31-40.                                                       6522 1451   57
                                                                  6522 1451   58
