  General methodology: The global approach considered in this     6522 1451   66
          work is presented in the following paper: Modern        6522 1451   67
          nuclear data evaluation with the TALYS code system,     6522 1451   68
          A.J. Koning and D. Rochman, Nuclear Data Sheets 113     6522 1451   69
          (2012) 2841.                                            6522 1451   70
                                                                  6522 1451   71
  MF2:  Resolved resonance range  (RRR)                           6522 1451   72
       The RRR was generated with TARES-1.31, compiled on         6522 1451   73
       12-10-2015 11:58:11 PM at Villingen  , Switzerland. The RRR6522 1451   74
       expands from 0 to 2.132391E+2 eV. A total of               6522 1451   75
       2 l-values are used and 200 resonances. The resonance      6522 1451   76
       formalism is multi-level Breit Wigner (MLBW).              6522 1451   77
       The ladder approach from the CALENDF code is used to       6522 1451   78
       generate statistical resonances in the unresolved          6522 1451   79
       resonance range. Therefore, the URR is translated into     6522 1451   80
       resolved resonance range. Explanations about the method    6522 1451   81
       can be found in the CALENDF manual: CEA-Report CEA-R-6277  6522 1451   82
       "CALENDF-2010: User manual" by J.C. Sublet, P. Ribon and   6522 1451   83
       M. Coste-Delcaux.                                          6522 1451   84
       The method of creating statistical resonances in the       6522 1451   85
       URR region is described in: "From average parameters to    6522 1451   86
       statistical resolved resonances", D. Rochman et al.,       6522 1451   87
       Annals of Nucl. Ene. 51 (2013) 60.                         6522 1451   88
       The s-wave average level spacing is 0.16345 eV and         6522 1451   89
       the s-wave neutron strength is 0.000213 1e-4.              6522 1451   90
                                                                  6522 1451   91
       After the ladder method, the retroactive method is applied 6522 1451   92
       to update the MF32 and MF2 with the SAMMY code.            6522 1451   93
                                                                  6522 1451   94
  MF32: Covariance file for resonance parameters                  6522 1451   95
        The compact format is used to represent the covariance    6522 1451   96
        information on the resonance parameters. Uncertainties    6522 1451   97
        come from compilations, EXFOR or existing libraries and   6522 1451   98
        correlations between parameters are obtained following    6522 1451   99
        the method presented in NIM/A 589 (2008) 85.              6522 1451  100
        SAMMY is used in the retroactive mode to update MF32.     6522 1451  101
