***************************** T A L Y S **************************6522 1451  157
                                                                  6522 1451  158
TALYS is a computer code system for the prediction and analysis   6522 1451  159
of nuclear reactions. TALYS simulates reactions that involve      6522 1451  160
neutrons, gamma-rays, protons, deuterons, tritons, helions and    6522 1451  161
alpha-particles, in the 1 keV - 200 MeV energy range. This is     6522 1451  162
achieved by implementing a suite of nuclear reaction models into  6522 1451  163
a single code system. This nuclear data file is based on a        6522 1451  164
theoretical analysis that utilizes the optical model, compound    6522 1451  165
nucleus statistical theory, fission, direct reactions and         6522 1451  166
pre-equilibrium processes, in combination with databases and      6522 1451  167
models for nuclear structure. The following output of TALYS is    6522 1451  168
stored in this data file:                                         6522 1451  169
                                                                  6522 1451  170
- Total, elastic and non-elastic cross sections                   6522 1451  171
- Inelastic cross sections to discrete states                     6522 1451  172
- Exclusive channel cross sections, e.g. (n,g), (n,2n), (n,np),.. 6522 1451  173
- Inelastic scattering angular distributions to discrete states   6522 1451  174
- Exclusive channel energy spectra                                6522 1451  175
- Exclusive channel double-differential spectra                   6522 1451  176
- Exclusive gamma production for discrete states and continuum    6522 1451  177
- Elastic scattering angular distributions                        6522 1451  178
- Recoil data                                                     6522 1451  179
- Total particle cross sections, e.g. (n,xn), (n,xp),..           6522 1451  180
- Total particle energy spectra                                   6522 1451  181
- Total particle double-differential spectra                      6522 1451  182
- Isomeric and ground state cross sections                        6522 1451  183
- Residual production cross sections                              6522 1451  184
                                                                  6522 1451  185
For a description of the used nuclear models and their            6522 1451  186
parameterization we refer to [kon12]. If for this specific        6522 1451  187
nuclide we deviate from the global parameterization, it is made   6522 1451  188
explicit above under Nuclide Specific Information.                6522 1451  189
                                                                  6522 1451  190
***************** F I L E   I N F O R M A T I O N ****************6522 1451  191
