##### MF1: GENERAL INFORMATION                                    6522 1451  193
                                                                  6522 1451  194
- MT451    : Descriptive data and directory                       6522 1451  195
                                                                  6522 1451  196
This text and the full directory of used MF/MT sections.          6522 1451  197
                                                                  6522 1451  198
##### MF2: RESONANCE PARAMETERS                                   6522 1451  199
                                                                  6522 1451  200
- MT151    : Resonance parameters                                 6522 1451  201
                                                                  6522 1451  202
Details about the origin of the resonance parameters for this     6522 1451  203
nuclide are given above in this description. In general, both a   6522 1451  204
Resolved and an Unresolved Resonance Range are given.             6522 1451  205
                                                                  6522 1451  206
##### MF3: REACTION CROSS SECTIONS                                6522 1451  207
                                                                  6522 1451  208
All the data present in the following MT-sections have been       6522 1451  209
calculated with TALYS, possibly normalized to experimental data.  6522 1451  210
If the maximal cross section in an excitation function over the   6522 1451  211
whole energy range does not exceed 1.e-9 b, the MT-number is not  6522 1451  212
included. Cross sections lower than 1.e-20 b are assumed to have  6522 1451  213
no physical meaning and are set to zero. All MT numbers extend up 6522 1451  214
to the highest incident energy.                                   6522 1451  215
The following reaction channels/MT numbers are generally included:6522 1451  216
                                                                  6522 1451  217
- MT1      : Total cross section                                  6522 1451  218
                                                                  6522 1451  219
Calculated with the optical model over the whole energy range,    6522 1451  220
or partly reproduced using experimental data.                     6522 1451  221
                                                                  6522 1451  222
- MT2      : Elastic scattering cross section                     6522 1451  223
                                                                  6522 1451  224
Obtained by subtracting the non-elastic cross section from the    6522 1451  225
total cross section.                                              6522 1451  226
                                                                  6522 1451  227
- MT3      : Non-elastic cross section                            6522 1451  228
                                                                  6522 1451  229
Calculated with the optical model over the whole energy range.    6522 1451  230
                                                                  6522 1451  231
- MT4      : Total inelastic cross section                        6522 1451  232
                                                                  6522 1451  233
Sum of MT=51-91.                                                  6522 1451  234
                                                                  6522 1451  235
- MT5      : (n,anything) cross section                           6522 1451  236
                                                                  6522 1451  237
MT5 contains the reactions which can not be stored in any other   6522 1451  238
MT-number. The information of MF3/MT5 can be combined with        6522 1451  239
MF6/MT5 to obtain residual production cross sections particle     6522 1451  240
production cross sections and (double-)differential cross         6522 1451  241
sections.                                                         6522 1451  242
                                                                  6522 1451  243
- MT16     : (n,2n) cross section                                 6522 1451  244
- MT17     : (n,3n) cross section                                 6522 1451  245
- MT22     : (n,na) cross section                                 6522 1451  246
- MT28     : (n,np) cross section                                 6522 1451  247
- MT51-90  : (n,n') cross section for 1st-40th excited state      6522 1451  248
- MT91     : (n,n') continuum cross section                       6522 1451  249
- MT102    : (n,gamma) cross section                              6522 1451  250
- MT103    : (n,p) cross section                                  6522 1451  251
- MT104    : (n,d) cross section                                  6522 1451  252
- MT105    : (n,t) cross section                                  6522 1451  253
- MT106    : (n,h) cross section                                  6522 1451  254
- MT107    : (n,a) cross section                                  6522 1451  255
- MT600-610: (n,p) cross section for 0th-10th excited state       6522 1451  256
- MT649    : (n,p) continuum cross section                        6522 1451  257
- MT650-655: (n,d) cross section for 0th-5th excited state        6522 1451  258
- MT699    : (n,d) continuum cross section                        6522 1451  259
- MT700-705: (n,t) cross section for 0th-5th excited state        6522 1451  260
- MT749    : (n,t) continuum cross section                        6522 1451  261
- MT750-755: (n,h) cross section for 0th-5th excited state        6522 1451  262
- MT799    : (n,h) continuum cross section                        6522 1451  263
- MT800-810: (n,a) cross section for 0th-10th excited state       6522 1451  264
- MT849    : (n,a) continuum cross section                        6522 1451  265
                                                                  6522 1451  266
##### MF4: ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS OF SECONDARY PARTICLES           6522 1451  267
                                                                  6522 1451  268
We use MF4 for the neutron scattering angular distribution for    6522 1451  269
discrete levels.                                                  6522 1451  270
                                                                  6522 1451  271
- MT2      : Elastic angular distribution                         6522 1451  272
                                                                  6522 1451  273
The flag LTT=3 is used to indicate a switch at some high energy,  6522 1451  274
generally 50 MeV, from a Legendre representation to a tabulated   6522 1451  275
representation. For incident energies below this energy, the      6522 1451  276
Legendre coefficients are given on a sufficiently precise energy  6522 1451  277
grid. They are a sum of calculated Legendre coefficients for      6522 1451  278
compound nucleus and shape-elastic scattering. For higher         6522 1451  279
incident energies, relative angular distributions are tabulated   6522 1451  280
on an angular grid.                                               6522 1451  281
                                                                  6522 1451  282
- MT51-70  : (n,n') angular distribution for 1st-20th state       6522 1451  283
- MT600-610: (n,p) angular distribution for 0th-10th state        6522 1451  284
- MT650-655: (n,d) angular distribution for 0th-5th state         6522 1451  285
- MT700-705: (n,t) angular distribution for 0th-5th state         6522 1451  286
- MT750-755: (n,h) angular distribution for 0th-5th state         6522 1451  287
- MT800-810: (n,a) angular distribution for 0th-10th state        6522 1451  288
                                                                  6522 1451  289
##### MF6: PRODUCT ENERGY-ANGLE DISTRIBUTIONS                     6522 1451  290
                                                                  6522 1451  291
In MF6 we store all secondary energy, angle, and energy-angle     6522 1451  292
distributions, as well as all residual and discrete + continuum   6522 1451  293
photon production cross sections for channels other than capture  6522 1451  294
(MT102) and reactions to discrete levels (MT51,etc.).             6522 1451  295
All data are generated with TALYS.                                6522 1451  296
                                                                  6522 1451  297
- MT5      : (n,anything) yields and energy-angle distributions   6522 1451  298
                                                                  6522 1451  299
MT5 contains, in this order,                                      6522 1451  300
For neutrons up to alpha particles and photons:                   6522 1451  301
- the production yields per particle for the whole energy range   6522 1451  302
- the secondary energy-angle distributions per particles which are6522 1451  303
  not represented by explicit MT numbers. On a secondary energy   6522 1451  304
  grid the relative emission spectra are given together with the  6522 1451  305
  parameters for the Kalbach systematics for angular              6522 1451  306
  distributions. Inelastic scattering cross sections for discrete 6522 1451  307
  states have been broadened and added to the continuum spectra.  6522 1451  308
For each residual product:                                        6522 1451  309
- the production yields for the whole energy range.               6522 1451  310
- the recoil                                                      6522 1451  311
These distributions can be multiplied with MF3/MT5 to get         6522 1451  312
the production cross sections and (double-)differential cross     6522 1451  313
sections.                                                         6522 1451  314
                                                                  6522 1451  315
- MT16     : (n,2n) energy-angle distr. and photon production     6522 1451  316
                                                                  6522 1451  317
First, for each type of outgoing particle, the (trivial) integer  6522 1451  318
particle yields are given. Next, on a sufficiently dense incident 6522 1451  319
energy grid the secondary energy-angle distributions are          6522 1451  320
specified by means of the relative emission spectra and the       6522 1451  321
parameters for the Kalbach systematics for angular distributions. 6522 1451  322
Next, the photon yield is tabulated as a function of incident     6522 1451  323
energy. For each incident energy, the photon production is given  6522 1451  324
for all discrete gamma lines present in the final nucleus. A      6522 1451  325
continuum photon distribution is added to this. We assume         6522 1451  326
isotropy for all produced gamma rays.                             6522 1451  327
                                                                  6522 1451  328
For the following MT-numbers, the same procedure as for MT16 is   6522 1451  329
followed:                                                         6522 1451  330
                                                                  6522 1451  331
- MT17 : (n,3n) energy-angle distr. and photon production         6522 1451  332
- MT22 : (n,na) energy-angle distr. and photon production         6522 1451  333
- MT28 : (n,np) energy-angle distr. and photon production         6522 1451  334
- MT91 : (n,n') continuum energy-angle distr. and phot. prod.     6522 1451  335
- MT649: (n,p) continuum energy-angle distr. and photon prod.     6522 1451  336
- MT699: (n,d) continuum energy-angle distr. and photon prod.     6522 1451  337
- MT749: (n,t) continuum energy-angle distr. and photon prod.     6522 1451  338
- MT809: (n,h) continuum energy-angle distr. and photon prod.     6522 1451  339
- MT849: (n,a) continuum energy-angle distr. and photon prod.     6522 1451  340
                                                                  6522 1451  341
##### MF8: RADIOACTIVE DECAY DATA                                 6522 1451  342
                                                                  6522 1451  343
For reactions to isomers, MF8 designates where the information    6522 1451  344
for isomeric versus ground state production, or residual          6522 1451  345
production can be found, i.e. for each MT number it points to     6522 1451  346
either MF6, MF9 or MF10.                                          6522 1451  347
                                                                  6522 1451  348
##### MF9: MULTIPLICITIES FOR PRODUCTION OF RADIOACTIVE NUCLIDES  6522 1451  349
                                                                  6522 1451  350
MF9 is used for isomer production by non-threshold reactions.     6522 1451  351
Final states with a lifetime that exceeds 1 second are treated    6522 1451  352
as isomer.                                                        6522 1451  353
                                                                  6522 1451  354
##### MF10: CROSS SECTIONS FOR PRODUCTION OF RADIOACTIVE NUCLIDES 6522 1451  355
                                                                  6522 1451  356
MF10 is used for isomer production by threshold reactions.        6522 1451  357
Final states with a lifetime that exceeds 1 second are treated    6522 1451  358
as isomer.                                                        6522 1451  359
                                                                  6522 1451  360
##### MF12: PHOTON PRODUCTION YIELD DATA                          6522 1451  361
                                                                  6522 1451  362
MF12 is used for the photon production for two types of reactions:6522 1451  363
- Reactions to discrete levels (MT51, etc.) For this transition   6522 1451  364
  probabilities are used (LO=2)                                   6522 1451  365
- Photons from neutron capture (MT102). Here multiplicities are   6522 1451  366
  given                                                           6522 1451  367
                                                                  6522 1451  368
##### MF14: PHOTON ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS                          6522 1451  369
                                                                  6522 1451  370
All photon production is considered as isotropic                  6522 1451  371
                                                                  6522 1451  372
##### MF15: PHOTON ENERGY SPECTRA                                 6522 1451  373
                                                                  6522 1451  374
For capture (MT102), the photon energy spectrum is given.         6522 1451  375
                                                                  6522 1451  376
##### MF32: COVARIANCES OF RESONANCE PARAMETERS                   6522 1451  377
                                                                  6522 1451  378
In MF32, we store the covariances of resonance parameters,        6522 1451  379
and more details are given above in this description.             6522 1451  380
                                                                  6522 1451  381
##### MF33: COVARIANCES OF NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS                 6522 1451  382
                                                                  6522 1451  383
In MF33, we store the covariances of most, but not all, reaction  6522 1451  384
channels that are given in MF3. All covariances are generated     6522 1451  385
with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates TALYS runs using    6522 1451  386
a Monte Carlo parameter method.                                   6522 1451  387
For each MT-number, the information consists of:                  6522 1451  388
1. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Ea (variances)                6522 1451  389
2. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Eb (correlations for the      6522 1451  390
   same reaction channel between different energies)              6522 1451  391
3. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Ea (correlations between      6522 1451  392
   different reaction channels for the same energy)               6522 1451  393
4. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Eb (correlations between      6522 1451  394
   different reaction channels for different energies)            6522 1451  395
Classes 1 and 2 are covered by NI-type subsubsections with        6522 1451  396
flag LB=5, followed by a LB=8 section which contains              6522 1451  397
the cross section variances multiplied by 1.e-3. Next, classes 3  6522 1451  398
and 4 are covered by flag LB=6 to account for the different       6522 1451  399
energy grids that two correlating MT-sections may have. Since     6522 1451  400
the total correlation matrix is fully symmetric, we only need to  6522 1451  401
include the correlation elements between different MT-numbers     6522 1451  402
once, and we do that in the subsection with the lowest of the     6522 1451  403
two MT-numbers. We include covariance information for all the     6522 1451  404
total cross sections, the lumped partial cross sections and the   6522 1451  405
individual inelastic cross sections per level (MT51,...). We do   6522 1451  406
not include covariances for MT600 and higher MT-numbers. For the  6522 1451  407
most important channels, we include cross-channel correlations.   6522 1451  408
                                                                  6522 1451  409
##### MF34: COVARIANCES OF ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS                  6522 1451  410
                                                                  6522 1451  411
In MF34, we store the covariances of the elastic scattering       6522 1451  412
angular distributions that are given in MF4/MT2. All covariances  6522 1451  413
are generated with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates       6522 1451  414
TALYS runs using a Monte Carlo parameter method. The tables are   6522 1451  415
restricted to MT2 and contain covariances for the first 6         6522 1451  416
Legendre coefficients. Both intra- and inter-correlations of the  6522 1451  417
various Legendre coefficients are given. As in MF33, the LB5      6522 1451  418
representation is used.                                           6522 1451  419
                                                                  6522 1451  420
##### MF40: COVARIANCES OF ISOMER PRODUCTION                      6522 1451  421
                                                                  6522 1451  422
For covariances of ground state and isomeric cross sections, the  6522 1451  423
same procedures as for MF33 are used.                             6522 1451  424
                                                                  6522 1451  425
